data.enText: very exciting or impressive (usually in a pleasant way); very surprising
a breathtaking view of the mountains
The scene was one of breathtaking beauty.
data.chText: 美妙的景色令人叹为观止。
他说话时的傲慢态度令人咋舌。

tr: tending to cause suspension of regular breathing

example.ex: The house has breathtaking views from every room...
example.tran: 这所房子的每个房间都能看到令人惊叹的美景。

example.ex: Some of their football was breathtaking, a delight to watch...
example.tran: 他们踢的一些比赛非常精彩，极具观赏性。

example.ex: He nevertheless completed the film with breathtaking speed.
example.tran: 但他还是以惊人的速度拍完了这部电影。

value.def: If you say that something is breathtaking, you are emphasizing that it is extremely beautiful or amazing.
value.tran: 令人兴奋的；激动人心的；壮观的

example.ex: ...the most breathtakingly beautiful scenery in Germany.

example.tran: 产自芬兰的一个出奇简单的小装置
